      "rationale": "No independent analyst review or double-blind simulation was performed. Use error not assessed; epistemic gap acknowledged at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model form uncertainty must be quantified, with sensitivity analysis demonstrating robustness of hemolysis prediction to model form choices.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected without systematic model-form sensitivity study. Power-law hemolysis model form uncertainty not quantified. Critical gap at MRL 5; not assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in all model input parameters (viscosity, hematocrit, pump geometry tolerances) must be propagated through Monte Carlo analysis to hemolysis QoI with full sensitivity indices reported.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo analysis performed on flow rate and rotational speed only; material property uncertainties (viscosity, hematocrit variation) and geometric tolerances not included in propagation. Partially assessed; formal factor assessment not completed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Number and diversity of experimental test samples must be sufficient to characterize biological variability in hemolysis response across the VAD operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Sample size characterization for biological variability in hemolysis not performed. Single batch of bovine blood used; inter-batch and inter-species variability not assessed. Not assessed at MRL 5."
